




{{See|Gay}}
==English==
=== Etymology ===
*''Gay'' is almost exclusively used today in its ''homosexual'' and related senses, and, latterly, in the sense of ''boring, etc''.  The earlier uses of ''festive'', ''colorful'', ''bright'' can still be found but have fallen out of fashion and are liable to misunderstanding.
*''Gay'' is preferred to ''homosexual'' by many gay people as their own term for themselves, claiming that ''homosexual'' is dated and evoking a time when ''homosexuality'' was considered a mental illness by the mental health community.
*From Latin ''gaius'', from Etruscan ''cai'', "I am glad".
<!--*Some object to sense 5 because they feel it encourages a negative perception of homosexuality while others feel that political correctness is hindering the natural progression of the language.-->

